misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes that saving the last element, shifting elements from right-to-left in a descending loop, then placing the saved last element into index 0 will rotate the array right by one, including wrap-around.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: No conceptual gap observed. This matches Java’s actual array indexing and assignment behavior: doing the shift from the end prevents overwriting values that are still needed, and the temporary variable preserves the wrapped element.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: No error; produces the expected shifted array for N>0 and safely handles N==0 by skipping the shift.
